WEBVTT

00:00:00.031 --> 00:00:01.715
The 737 MAX was sold as a

00:00:01.715 --> 00:00:04.850
familiar airplane. That was the commercial

00:00:04.850 --> 00:00:07.892
promise. Airlines could keep crews,

00:00:07.892 --> 00:00:10.582
schedules, and training close to the old

00:00:10.582 --> 00:00:14.249
737. Then Boeing put larger CFM LEAP

00:00:14.249 --> 00:00:16.312
engines on the aircraft.

00:00:17.254 --> 00:00:19.421
They sat farther forward and higher on

00:00:19.421 --> 00:00:20.911
the wing, and under certain

00:00:20.911 --> 00:00:23.146
high-angle-of-attack conditions, the jet

00:00:23.146 --> 00:00:24.704
could pitch up differently.

00:00:25.207 --> 00:00:27.350
MCAS was built to make that new

00:00:27.350 --> 00:00:30.093
behavior feel familiar. But the system

00:00:30.093 --> 00:00:32.407
could move the stabilizer from one

00:00:32.407 --> 00:00:35.857
angle-of-attack sensor. Pilots were not

00:00:35.857 --> 00:00:37.840
clearly trained that it existed by name.

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:41.606
After Lion Air 610, the warning still

00:00:41.606 --> 00:00:44.130
was not reclassified fast enough as an

00:00:44.130 --> 00:00:47.192
architectural problem. The plane had

00:00:47.192 --> 00:00:50.107
changed. The story told to the people

00:00:50.107 --> 00:00:51.031
flying it had not.

00:00:51.832 --> 00:00:54.996
Small causes, massive consequences.
